The paper introduces a new data structure called the Deletable Bloom filter (DlBF), which is based on the popular Bloom filter. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the memory consumption and false-negative-free deletions, which are related to database systems and cryptography, respectively. Hence, it could also belong to the cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the encoding of information, which is related to information theory, and the probabilistic filter applications, which are related to artificial intelligence. Therefore, it could also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
